Ovipositor slightly shorter than abdomen, lacking rows of long setae on posterior third, on external side of baculi. Spermatheca (
Figure 3f
) subcylindrical, small (
0.54 mm
); nodulus almost indistinct and ramus (prominence at gland entrance) incipient; spermathecal duct about 4× as long as spermatheca.
